# Room 7 Windows Fundamentals Part 1

## Task 1 Windows Editions

Windows has evolved since 1985, becoming the dominant OS for home and corporate use.
Key Versions:
Windows XP: widely used, long support cycle.
Windows Vista: major overhaul, poorly received.
Windows 7: stable, widely adopted after XP’s end-of-life.
Windows 8.x: short-lived, similar fate to Vista.
Windows 10: mainstream OS, retirement set for October 14, 2025.
Windows 11: current desktop OS (Home & Pro editions).
Server Editions: current version is Windows Server 2025.
VM Edition Used in Lab: Windows Server 2019 Standard.

