## Findings
- Windows provides both modern (Settings) and legacy (Control Panel) interfaces for system management.
- Task Manager is essential for monitoring performance and troubleshooting.
- NTFS enhances security and reliability compared to older file systems.
- UAC reduces malware risks by requiring elevation prompts.
- System32 and user account management are critical for OS stability and security.

## Mitigation / Practical Application
- Use Settings for common tasks, but rely on Control Panel for advanced configurations.
- Regularly check Task Manager to identify resource-heavy or suspicious processes.
- Apply NTFS permissions carefully to enforce least privilege.
- Keep UAC enabled to prevent unauthorized system changes.
- Avoid tampering with System32 to maintain OS integrity.

